# Branching Flow Logic

Branching logic allows a flow to follow different paths based on conditions.

## What is Branching?

Branching is implemented using Decision elements in Salesforce Flow.

### Example: Customer Support Priority Flow

```text
New Support Case
        ↓
Priority Decision
        ↓
 ┌───────────────┬───────────────┬───────────────┐
 │ High          │ Medium        │ Low           │
 ↓               ↓               ↓
Escalate     Assign Team     Queue Case
```

---

## Example: Loan Application Flow

```text
Loan Application
        ↓
Credit Score Check
        ↓
 ┌───────────────┬───────────────┐
 │ Score ≥ 750   │ Score < 750   │
 ↓               ↓
Approved     Manual Review
```

---

## Advantages of Branching Logic

* Dynamic business processes
* Better decision-making
* Reduced manual intervention
* Improved efficiency

